fields.name: Tile Cement
fields.description: Eurofix tile-cement is a formulated dry cementitious based single component  mortar that is mixed with water to form a consistent paste for problem-free tile installation.
fields.benefit:
- Economical in use.
- Shrinkage cracks are minimized in concrete and mortar.
- Improves cohesion and hence reduces the segregation.
- Easily trowellable.
- Hassle free Laying of tiles with euroﬁx tile cement is easy since only water is required to be added.
- No hacking of the required to achieve the required bonding.
fields.application_field:
- For bonding small and medium sized ﬂoor and wall tiles, marbles, natural stones and decorative bricks.
-Intended for both interior and exterior.

fields.name: Waterproof Grout
fields.description:
Eurofix waterproof grout is a cement based, ploymer modiﬁed grout mortar.

Available in White, Cream, Beige, Grey, Brown, Satin Grey, Black, Blue and dark-grey.

Custom grout colors can also be pre-ordered.
fields.benefit:
- Water repellent in nature reduces seepage and maintain hygienic conditions.
- Cement based and polymer modiﬁed.
- Pot life 1 hour
fields.application_field:
- For grouting up to 6 mm width of coating materials such as ceramic tiles, , natural stone, granite and marble.
- Intended for both interior and exterior.

fields.name: Ready To Use Cement
fields.description: Euroﬁx ready to use cement as a premixed solution to substitute for the traditional  mixing of sand and cement. It is speciﬁcally manufactured and supplied as a single product which is ready to use by just mixing with water at the site.
fields.benefit:
- Hassle-free: Euroﬁx Ready To Use Cement is ready to use by just mixing with water at the site. Additionally, It is easy to handle, store and transport.
- Consistent high quality: Ready to use cement is a machine mixed material where high consistent quality is ensured through the mixing of material.
- Polymerized: Special additives are added to enhance weather resistance by enhancing their water resistance capabilities.
- Economical: It Save cost since less paint is required, less labor is paid for, no future maintenance cost hence saving at least 25% of construction cost.
- Euroﬁx Has a higher bonding strength making plaster and ﬂoor is more durable compared to those ﬁxed with ordinary sand cement mixture.
- Multipurpose: Can be used for both interior and exterior.
fields.application_field:
- Plastering works.
- Masonary works.
- Floor screeding.
- Laying of blocks and bricks..

fields.name: Hollow pots
fields.description: Hollow pots are used to make Hollow slabs. This is a type of slab that is constructed with hollow pots. Hollow pot slabs are usually constructed with fewer concrete and reinforcement compare with solid slab. Hollow blocks are used to fill portions of the slab thickness; this results in deeper the amount of concrete and hence the weight of the slab
fields.benefit:
• Reduced slab weight due to reduced amount of concrete below neutral axis.
• Ease of construction, especially when all beams are hidden beams.
• Economical due to reduced material usage (reinforcement and concrete)
• Attractive soffit appearance if exposed
• Improved insulation for sound and heat
• Decrease in construction time and labor cost.
fields.application_field: Ideal for Office buildings, auditoriums, hotels, commercial buildings, residential buildings, appartments and educational facilities

fields.name: Cabro Paving Blocks
fields.description: Cabros are  one of the most popular flexible surface treatment options for exterior pavement applications. These blocks are aesthetically pleasing, comfortable to walk on, extremely durable, and easy to maintain.
fields.benefit:
-  Paver blocks do not need special maintenance as compared to concrete or asphalt surfaces. A simple water washing can help keep the blocks clean and bright.
-  Paver blocks are very durable, and if they are adequately interlocked, they can easily last for about 20 years. Paver blocks can withstand hefty vehicular load as well.
-   Paver blocks are available in different shapes and colors, making it very versatile. These blocks can be used at residential as well as commercial premises.
-  Paver blocks are slip-resistant and skid resistant.
-  Paver blocks can be used in any weather conditions.
-   These paver blocks are very easy to install and do not need any special equipment for its installation.
 -  The most important advantage of paver blocks is that they can be easily replaced. If one of the blocks gets damaged, it can be easily removed and replaced with another one.
fields.application_field: - Ideal for Footpaths, , Public Gardens/Parks, Shopping Complexes, Bus Terminus Parking areas, and Railway Platform, Light traffic areas like Office Driveway, Housing Colony Roads, Office/Commercial Complexes, Car Parks, Rural Roads, Private Drive Ways, Domestic Cars, Parks and. Walkways,

fields.name: Interlocking Blocks
fields.description:
Interlocking blocks is the latest advancement in today's Wall Construction. These blocks are 'locked' against each other without the use of cement mortar.
Interlocking blocks are accelerating the construction of low cost houses in Kenya, with more builders embracing the technique that lowers building costs by up to 60%.
fields.benefit:
- Cost effective, since less mortar cement is required for joining and plastering.
- Enviomental friendly.
- Durable
-  Low maintainance
- First construction
- High strength

fields.name: Hollow Blocks
fields.description: Hollow Block is a type of concrete block used for building internal and external walls.
fields.benefit:
-  Hollow block helps in saving construction material, hence reduces the construction cost.
-  The hollow block will give a different look as it reduces the energy bill to create an environmentally friendly environment in the building.
-   Solid hollow blocks require less maintenance and provide insulation from sound, heat, and fire-resistant.
-   The joints in these blocks require less cement mortar, little or no plastering thus speeding up the construction process.
 -  High dimensional accuracy and consistent finish make it an ideal building material for building load-bearing structures and building partition walls.
 -  These hollow concrete blocks have high-stress bearing capacity hence widely used in building construction practices.
 -  Concrete hollow blocks are lightweight hence used in the construction of homes in earthquake-prone areas.
 -  These blocks are more cost-effective than other traditional wall systems or wall construction systems.
 -  It is high quality, high strength, uniform size, and shape.
 -  It is completely energy-efficient does not require any non-renewable resources for its production.
 -  Also, it does not disturb the ecosystem so they are either environmentally friendly or eco-friendly since the waste and local resources can be used for its manufacture or production.
 -  It can also be manufactured at the site.
 -  Hollow space in blocks makes masonry work soundproof, heatproof and damp proofing.
fields.application_field:
-   Hollow blocks can be used in load-bearing structures, low-rise residential, office buildings, bungalows, shelter units for rural housing, tall buildings, institutional buildings, warehouses, etc.
-   It is used in frame structures such as high-rise residential apartments, office buildings, market premises, hospitals, and hotels, etc.
